 To show that the eigenvalues of 
\begin_inset Formula $P^{-1}AP$
\end_inset

 are the same as the eigenvalues of 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 is a matter of a calculation.
 For any value 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

,
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
\det(P^{-1}AP-\lambda I) & =\det(P^{-1}AP-P^{-1}(\lambda I)P)\\
 & =\det(P^{-1}(A-\lambda I)P)\\
 & =\det(P^{-1})\cdot\dot{\det(A-\lambda I)}\cdot\det P\\
 & =\det(A-\lambda I)
\end{align*}

\end_inset

so the characteristic equations of 
\begin_inset Formula $P^{-1}AP$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 are equal making the eigenvalues of 
\begin_inset Formula $P^{-1}AP$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
