 the images of the coffee cup in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{2}$
\end_inset

 can be derived.
 They will also be a collection of reflections, shears, and scalings.
 Rotation in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{3}$
\end_inset

 can be accomplished by a compostion of scalings and shears just as in 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{R}^{2}$
\end_inset

.
 Noninvertible 
\begin_inset Formula $3\times3$
